(4216, '_transient_dash_4077549d03da2e451c8b5f002294ff51', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://wordpress.org/news/2016/01/wordpress-4-4-1-security-and-maintenance-release/''>WordPress 4.4.1 Security and Maintenance Release</a> <span class="rss-date">January 6, 2016</span><div class="rssSummary">WordPress 4.4.1 is now available. This is a security release for all previous versions and we strongly encourage you to update your sites immediately. WordPress versions 4.4 and earlier are affected by a cross-site scripting vulnerability that could allow a site to be compromised. This was reported by Crtc4L. There were also several non-security bug fixes: Emoji [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/atom-editor-package-adds-autocomplete-for-wordpress-actions-and-filters''>WPTavern: Atom Editor Package Adds Autocomplete for WordPress Actions and Filters</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2016/01/18/wordpress-php7-and-updates-via-php-ssh2/''>Dougal Campbell: WordPress, PHP7, and Updates via php-ssh2</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/wpshouts-2016-webhosting-survey-results-show-specialized-hosts-are-doing-well''>WPTavern: WPShout’s 2016 Webhosting Survey Results Show Specialized Hosts Are Doing Well</a></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li class=''dashboard-news-plugin''><span>Popular Plugin:</span> <a href=''https://wordpress.org/plugins/siteorigin-panels/'' class=''dashboard-news-plugin-link''>Page Builder by SiteOrigin</a>&nbsp;<span>(<a href=''plugin-install.php?tab=plugin-information&amp;plugin=siteorigin-panels&amp;_wpnonce=4fffb89065&amp;TB_iframe=true&amp;width=600&amp;height=800'' class=''thickbox'' title=''Page Builder by SiteOrigin''>Install</a>)</span></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
