(205, 1, '2014-12-18 22:27:34', '2014-12-19 03:27:34', '<div>\r\n\r\nThe IBOUTLET allows you to change properties of a control while the Action is used for an event to trigger code basically do something.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it''s text property you could change it''s size, colour, font etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'what is the difference between outlet and action', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-the-difference-between-outlet-and-action', '', '', '2014-12-18 22:28:18', '2014-12-19 03:28:18', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=205', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(206, 1, '2014-12-18 22:27:34', '2014-12-19 03:27:34', '<div><p>The&nbsp;IBOUTLET allows you to change properties of a control while the Action is used for an event to trigger code basically do something.&nbsp;</p><p>So you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it''s text property you could change it''s size, colour, font etc.</p><p> You would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .</p><p>Basically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.<br></p></div>', 'what is the difference between outlet and action', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '205-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-18 22:27:34', '2014-12-19 03:27:34', '', 205, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/205-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(207, 1, '2014-12-18 22:28:18', '2014-12-19 03:28:18', '<div>\r\n\r\nThe IBOUTLET allows you to change properties of a control while the Action is used for an event to trigger code basically do something.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it''s text property you could change it''s size, colour, font etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'what is the difference between outlet and action', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '205-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-18 22:28:18', '2014-12-19 03:28:18', '', 205, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/205-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
