(81, 1, '2014-11-29 22:34:12', '2014-11-30 03:34:12', '<div><p>JuliusJS&nbsp;is a speech recognition library for the web. It is an opinionated port of Julius to JavaScript. It actively listens to the user to transcribe what they are saying through a callback. All recognition is done in-browser through a Worker. It is licensed under MIT License.<br></p><p><br></p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2183804483/facebook_logo_normal.png" class="fr-fin"></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/H94w" target="_blank">WebAppers</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via&nbsp;twitter.com</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Julius JS - A Speech Recognition Library for the Web<a href="http://zocle.us/I94w" target="_blank">bit.ly/1vTSnxN</a></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Date">11/28/2014 8:59 AM</div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', 'Julius JS – A Speech Recognition Library for the Web', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'julius-js-a-speech-recognition-library-for-the-web', '', '', '2014-12-22 16:55:52', '2014-12-22 21:55:52', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=81', 0, 'post', '', 3),
