(89, 1, '2014-12-01 15:28:17', '2014-12-01 20:28:17', '<div>\n\nThis article examines two implementations of a logic puzzle written in Swift. The first example uses an imperative programming style, which is the style familiar to most iOS developers. Then we see the same small program written in a functional style, which is facilitated by several Swift language features.\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/477125695663915008/faa0G2Ij_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/a94w" target="_blank">Coding in Swift</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">★★ Functional Programming in Swift by <a href="http://zocle.us/b94w" target="_blank">@bach4life</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/c94w" target="_blank">ijoshsmith.com/2014/11/30/get…</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/A94w" target="_blank">#swift</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/B94w" target="_blank">#swiftlang</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/01/2014 2:40 AM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'Getting into functional programming with Swift', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'getting-into-functional-programming-with-swift', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:09:25', '2014-12-17 19:09:25', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=89', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2014-12-01 15:41:29', '2014-12-01 20:41:29', '<div>\n\nEvery Possible Way to Define a JavaScript Function\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/505048043377262592/VMUR5EzE_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/e94w" target="_blank">JavaScript Daily</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Every Possible Way to Define a JavaScript Function: <a href="http://zocle.us/f94w" target="_blank">bryanbraun.com/2014/11/27/eve…</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">11/30/2014 4:41 PM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'Every Possible Way to Define a JavaScript Function', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'every-possible-way-to-define-a-javascript-function', '', '', '2014-12-22 16:55:42', '2014-12-22 21:55:42', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=92', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2014-12-01 18:43:53', '2014-12-01 23:43:53', '<div><p>CSS3 have made designing web more exciting with the introduction of new properties. While you might know of the popular ones, such as the&nbsp;box-shadow,&nbsp;border-radius, and&nbsp;transform, there are plenty more properties that you may not have heard of or tried, but would be glad to know of its existence.<br></p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/B3ylY_FIcAElrUt.png" class="fr-fin"></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/o94w" target="_blank">SitePoint</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via&nbsp;twitter.com</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Via Versioning: 10 CSS3 properties you should probably know: <a href="http://zocle.us/p94w" target="_blank">hongkiat.com/blog/css3-prop…</a><a href="http://zocle.us/q94w" target="_blank">sitepoint.com/versioning</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/r94w" target="_blank">pic.twitter.com/QSL7oSJRKb</a></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/01/2014 1:35 PM</div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', '10 Hidden CSS3 Properties You Should Know', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '10-hidden-css3-properties-you-should-know', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:09:07', '2014-12-17 19:09:07', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=95', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(97, 1, '2014-12-02 15:56:09', '2014-12-02 20:56:09', '<div>\n\nreorderable grid view solution implemented with swift.\nits UIScrollView subclass, its not a collection view layout.\nautomatically sets horizontal item spacing by item widths. so items must be fixed-width.\nalso sets automatically its content size.\nif you call <code>gridView?.invalidateLayout()</code> after orientation changed, it will lays out the grid by new orientation.\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/501807316644032513/Rq1tEak-_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/fA4w" target="_blank">Swift Toolbox</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">ReorderableGridView-Swiftreorderable grid view solution implemented with swift. its UIScrollView subclass, its not<a href="http://zocle.us/gA4w" target="_blank">github.com/cemolcay/Reord…</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/02/2014 10:44 AM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'reorderable grid view solution implemented with swift.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'reorderable-grid-view-solution-implemented-with-swift', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:08:59', '2014-12-17 19:08:59', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=97', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(102, 1, '2014-12-02 16:08:46', '2014-12-02 21:08:46', '<div>\n\nWhereas a two-dimensional set of co-ordinates has an x-axis and y-axis, a three-dimensional set of co-ordinates as found in the CATransform3D Core Animation Functions has x, y and z axes. A z-axis comes outwards, or upwards, depending on which way you look at it.\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/477125695663915008/faa0G2Ij_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/oA4w" target="_blank">Coding in Swift</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">The World of CATransform3D: Translation, Rotation and Scaling <a href="http://zocle.us/pA4w" target="_blank">sketchytech.blogspot.com/2014/12/a-swif…</a> via <a href="http://zocle.us/qA4w" target="_blank">@sketchyTech</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/A94w" target="_blank">#swift</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/B94w" target="_blank">#swiftlang</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/01/2014 12:42 PM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'The World of CATransform3D: Translation, Rotation and Scaling', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-world-of-catransform3d-translation-rotation-and-scaling', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:08:50', '2014-12-17 19:08:50', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.wordpress.com/?p=102', 0, 'post', '', 0),
