(185, 1, '2014-12-17 14:08:50', '2014-12-17 19:08:50', '<div>\n\nWhereas a two-dimensional set of co-ordinates has an x-axis and y-axis, a three-dimensional set of co-ordinates as found in the CATransform3D Core Animation Functions has x, y and z axes. A z-axis comes outwards, or upwards, depending on which way you look at it.\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/477125695663915008/faa0G2Ij_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/oA4w" target="_blank">Coding in Swift</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">The World of CATransform3D: Translation, Rotation and Scaling <a href="http://zocle.us/pA4w" target="_blank">sketchytech.blogspot.com/2014/12/a-swif…</a> via <a href="http://zocle.us/qA4w" target="_blank">@sketchyTech</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/A94w" target="_blank">#swift</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/B94w" target="_blank">#swiftlang</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/01/2014 12:42 PM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'The World of CATransform3D: Translation, Rotation and Scaling', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '102-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:08:50', '2014-12-17 19:08:50', '', 102, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/102-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2014-12-17 14:08:59', '2014-12-17 19:08:59', '<div>\n\nreorderable grid view solution implemented with swift.\nits UIScrollView subclass, its not a collection view layout.\nautomatically sets horizontal item spacing by item widths. so items must be fixed-width.\nalso sets automatically its content size.\nif you call <code>gridView?.invalidateLayout()</code> after orientation changed, it will lays out the grid by new orientation.\n<blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;">\n<div class="zocle-editor-content">\n<div class="sort-element-content">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter">\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img class="fr-fin" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/501807316644032513/Rq1tEak-_normal.png" alt="" /></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Details">\n<h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/fA4w" target="_blank">Swift Toolbox</a></h2>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via twitter.com</div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">ReorderableGridView-Swiftreorderable grid view solution implemented with swift. its UIScrollView subclass, its not<a href="http://zocle.us/gA4w" target="_blank">github.com/cemolcay/Reord…</a></div>\n<div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/02/2014 10:44 AM</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n</div>', 'reorderable grid view solution implemented with swift.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:08:59', '2014-12-17 19:08:59', '', 97, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/97-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(187, 1, '2014-12-17 14:09:07', '2014-12-17 19:09:07', '<div><p>CSS3 have made designing web more exciting with the introduction of new properties. While you might know of the popular ones, such as the&nbsp;box-shadow,&nbsp;border-radius, and&nbsp;transform, there are plenty more properties that you may not have heard of or tried, but would be glad to know of its existence.<br></p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/B3ylY_FIcAElrUt.png" class="fr-fin"></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/o94w" target="_blank">SitePoint</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_URL">Via&nbsp;twitter.com</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Via Versioning: 10 CSS3 properties you should probably know: <a href="http://zocle.us/p94w" target="_blank">hongkiat.com/blog/css3-prop…</a><a href="http://zocle.us/q94w" target="_blank">sitepoint.com/versioning</a> <a href="http://zocle.us/r94w" target="_blank">pic.twitter.com/QSL7oSJRKb</a></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Date">12/01/2014 1:35 PM</div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', '10 Hidden CSS3 Properties You Should Know', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-17 14:09:07', '2014-12-17 19:09:07', '', 95, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
