(261, 1, '2015-01-21 13:18:39', '2015-01-21 18:18:39', '<div><p><br></p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content" data-og-id="1421864174970" data-uniqid="1421864174970" contenteditable="false"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_RSS"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><a title="Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way" alt="Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way" href="http://zocle.us/9S4w" target="_blank">		    							<img src="http://dab1nmslvvntp.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/142150824201.gif" class="rssShowImgSrc" data-num="1">		    						</a></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/9S4w" target="_blank">Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Bruno Skvorc shows you the best way to get started developing new PHP packages with the help of The PHP League and a friendly checklist</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Date"><time>01/21/2015 1:18 PM</time></div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', 'Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'starting-a-new-php-package-the-right-way', '', '', '2015-01-21 13:18:39', '2015-01-21 18:18:39', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=261', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(262, 1, '2015-01-21 13:18:39', '2015-01-21 18:18:39', '<div><p><br></p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content" data-og-id="1421864174970" data-uniqid="1421864174970" contenteditable="false"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_RSS"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_Left"><a title="Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way" alt="Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way" href="http://zocle.us/9S4w" target="_blank">		    							<img src="http://dab1nmslvvntp.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/142150824201.gif" class="rssShowImgSrc" data-num="1">		    						</a></div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/9S4w" target="_blank">Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_Teaser">Bruno Skvorc shows you the best way to get started developing new PHP packages with the help of The PHP League and a friendly checklist</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Date"><time>01/21/2015 1:18 PM</time></div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', 'Starting a New PHP Package The Right Way', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '261-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-21 13:18:39', '2015-01-21 18:18:39', '', 261, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/261-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(263, 1, '2015-01-27 00:33:47', '2015-01-27 05:33:47', '<div><p>Sometimes you need to change a file in Git and maybe you don''t want to commit that change.</p><p>So you can do something like this:</p><p><span style="color: #FF0000;">git update-index --assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p><p>If you want to stop ignoring changes in the file, use the following command:<br><span style="color: #FF0000;">git update-index --no-assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p></div>', 'Temporarily Ignore Changes for a File in Git', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'temporarily-ignore-changes-for-a-file-in-git', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:54:58', '2015-01-27 16:54:58', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=263', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(264, 1, '2015-01-27 00:33:47', '2015-01-27 05:33:47', '<div><p>Sometimes you need to change a file in Git and maybe you don''t want to commit that change.</p><p>So you can do something like this:</p><p><span style="color: #FF0000;">git update-index --assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p><p>If you want to stop ignoring changes in the file, use the following command:<br><span style="color: #FF0000;">git update-index --no-assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p></div>', 'Temporarily Ignore Changes for a File in Git', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '263-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 00:33:47', '2015-01-27 05:33:47', '', 263, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/263-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(312, 1, '2015-04-02 19:11:46', '2015-04-03 00:11:46', '<div><p>We can using Digital Ocean server install LEMP environment for PHP project.</p><blockquote class="zocle_blockquote" style="clear:both;"><div class="zocle-editor-content" data-og-id="1428019844390" data-uniqid="1428019844390" contenteditable="false"><div class="sort-element-content"><div class="Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_RSS"><div class="Zocle_Content_Image_None">			    					<a title="How To Install Linux, nginx, MySQL, PHP (LEMP) stack on Ubuntu 12.04 | DigitalOcean" alt="How To Install Linux, nginx, MySQL, PHP (LEMP) stack on Ubuntu 12.04 | DigitalOcean" href="http://zocle.us/Fn4w" target="_blank">			    						<img src="" class="rssShowImgSrc fr-fin" data-num="1">			    					</a>			    				</div><div class="Zocle_Content_Details"><h2 class="Zocle_Content_Headline"><a href="http://zocle.us/Fn4w" target="_blank">How To Install Linux, nginx, MySQL, PHP (LEMP) stack on Ubuntu 12.04 | DigitalOcean</a></h2><div class="Zocle_Content_Date"><time>04/02/2015 8:12 PM</time></div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>', 'How To Install Linux, nginx, MySQL, PHP (LEMP) stack on Ubuntu 12.04', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-install-linux-nginx-mysql-php-lemp-stack-on-ubuntu-12-04', '', '', '2015-04-02 19:11:46', '2015-04-03 00:11:46', '', 0, 'http://blog.zhexiao.space/?p=312', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(266, 1, '2015-01-27 11:53:48', '2015-01-27 16:53:48', '<div><p>To install both Sass and Compass in Ubuntu 12.10, Ubuntu 13.04 or Debian you will first need to install ruby and ruby gems packages.<br><br><span style="color: #FF0000;">sudo apt-get install ruby-full rubygems1.8<br></span>Now you can download and install sass and compass with the following commands. (Gem is a package management system for ruby apps think of it as apt-get for ruby)<br><br><span style="color: #FF0000;">sudo gem install sass<br>sudo gem install compass</span></p><p><br></p><p><br><br></p></div>', 'Install Sass and Compass on ubuntu', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'install-sass-and-compass-on-ubuntu', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:54:51', '2015-01-27 16:54:51', '', 0, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=266', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(267, 1, '2015-01-27 11:53:48', '2015-01-27 16:53:48', '<div><p>To install both Sass and Compass in Ubuntu 12.10, Ubuntu 13.04 or Debian you will first need to install ruby and ruby gems packages.<br><br><span style="color: #FF0000;">sudo apt-get install ruby-full rubygems1.8<br></span>Now you can download and install sass and compass with the following commands. (Gem is a package management system for ruby apps think of it as apt-get for ruby)<br><br><span style="color: #FF0000;">sudo gem install sass<br>sudo gem install compass</span></p><p><br></p><p><br><br></p></div>', 'Install Sass and Compass on ubuntu', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '266-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:53:48', '2015-01-27 16:53:48', '', 266, 'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/266-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
